history.content: CS 160 has basically hit its 70% enrollment mark (@3831), so until GSI hiring is finished, the best you can do is waitlist.

children.subject:
I am a rising declared CS junior and was having the same problem as @anon

I had to waitlist for CS 160 and am surprised that I had to do this since it is just Phase 1 registration. How many students get off the CS160 waitlist?
Can someone please actually answer the question? How many students get off the waitlist? Who is the "available seats" reserved for as per the error message?
EDIT: Who is the "available seats" reserved for as per the error message if it is not letting CS/EECS majors enroll?

As the above answer states: they are not reserved for anyone. They are waiting for TA hiring to finish (probably around August). This is the policy for almost all upper-divs, as described in the link.

If the class expands as projected, then the seats will free up. Otherwise, they will not.

I don't know of any reason to not expect that a "typical" number of students get off of the waitlist.

Trouble enrolling into CS 160

I am a rising CS declared junior and want to enroll for CS 160. When I try to register for the class, I get this message: 

Error: You are unable to enroll in this class at this time. Available seats are reserved and you do not meet the reserve capacity requirements. If a wait list is available, you may still be placed on the waitlist for this class. To do this, select Add Another Class to return to step 1. Select the class link, select the wait list option and resubmit your request.

What does this mean? 

The Piazza post "F17 Enrollment: Upper Div COMPSCI Classes" says: I believe hiring is in process for lecturers for 161 and 160 so enrollments for those classes will proceed normally.

I had to waitlist for CS 160 and am surprised since it is during the Phase 1 registration. How many students get off the CS160 waitlist?

Error When Enrolling in CS186

I had my phase 2 today and when I tried enrolling in CS186, I got:

Error: You are unable to enroll in this class at this time. Available seats are reserved and you do not meet the reserve capacity requirements. If a wait list is available, you may still be placed on the waitlist for this class. To do this, select Add Another Class to return to step 1. Select the class link, select the wait list option and resubmit your request.

There still seem to be open spots according to Berkeleytime, and I shouldn't have any restrictions since I'm declared EECS. Is this a glitch or am I not able to enroll?
